  "subject": "Fix race condition while stopping the thread",
  "commit_message": "Fix race condition while stopping the thread\n\nWhen executing stop() and start() right after each other or\nin parallel by different threads the busPollerthread may not\nnotice its change and keep executing. Example:\n\nThread #1  \t      \t   \t      Thread #2\n       \t\t\t\t      inside fetch()\nthis.alive = false; [stop()]\nthis.alive = true; [start()]\n\n\t\t\t\t\t// false\n\t\t\t\t\tif (!alive) {\n\t\t\t\t\t   break;\n\t\t\t\t\t}\n\nEven through yield() is used in stop() it doesn't guarantee\ncorrectness.\n\nLet's fix this by using thread interrupt to ensure that request to\nstop the thread never gets lost\n\nChange-Id: I6c2339e49f0348a50b87c7a26f4cba20c7a38cb6\nIssue-ID: POLICY-1387\nSigned-off-by: Krzysztof Opasiak <k.opasiak@samsung.com>\n",
