        "timestamp": "2019-02-14 20:33:39.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 6: -Code-Review\n\n> (4 comments)\n\nPersonally, I'd create a subclass of Thread containing everything it needs, including a \"stop\" flag, implemented via a CountDownLatch.  Create and store the thread object when it's running.  Stop it and store null when done.  Don't bother with interrupts.  Could also override isAlive() to check that it's non-null and the thread, itself, is alive.",
        "patchset_number": 6
      },
