        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2019-02-14 20:51:07.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 6:\n\n> > (4 comments)\n > \n > Personally, I'd create a subclass of Thread containing everything\n > it needs, including a \"stop\" flag, implemented via a\n > CountDownLatch.  Create and store the thread object when it's\n > running.  Stop it and store null when done.  Don't bother with\n > interrupts.  Could also override isAlive() to check that it's\n > non-null and the thread, itself, is alive.\n\nand, of course, the run() method would be moved into the thread subclass",
        "patchset_number": 6
